\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 51. G. mirum} Rech. fil., {\i Bot. Jahrb.}{\b  69}: 512 (1939). Stems up to 120 cm, usually robust and strongly branched, densely villous at base with hairs more than 1 mm; internodes up to 10 cm with whitish angles. Middle cauline leaves 15-25 × 1-2 mm, linear, the lower oblong; leaves with a short hyaline apiculum, and the margin slightly revolute. Inflorescence very broadly ovoid, with very long and patent branches; pedicels c. 2-4(-6) mm, slender. Corolla 1·5-2·5 mm in diameter. 2n = 22.{\i  Sub-mediterranean scrub. • S.E. part of Balkan peninsula.} Bu Gr Ju.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 52. G. scabrifolium} (Boiss.) Hausskn.,{\i  Mitt. Thür. Bot. Ver.} nov. ser., {\b 5}: 120 (1893). Stems 50-80 cm, usually with short hairs at base (rarely with longer hairs), erect, usually strongly branched. Leaves 7-20 × 0·5-1·5(-2) mm, linear, with hyaline apiculum of medium length; midrib prominent; margin revolute. Inflorescence oblong or ovoid, with erect branches. Pedicels as long as or shorter than diameter of corolla. Corolla (2-)3-5 mm in diameter, yellowish-white. 2n = 22, 44. {\i Dry places. S. part of Balkan peninsula.} Bu Gr Ju.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28   This polymorphic species seems to contain a number of variants which may deserve taxonomic recognition. One, with stiffly erect and white-angled stems, short leaves and dense inflorescences ranges from S.E. Macedonia to W. Anatolia. Another has more patent branches and longer leaves; it is diploid and occurs in Macedonia and adjacent W. Bulgaria. In the higher mountains of Thraki and on Thasos there is a third, tetraploid variant with less branching, shorter internodes, slightly wider and shorter leaves, and less apiculate corolla-lobes.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 53. G. peloponnesiacum} Ehrend. & Krendl, {\i Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc.}{\b  68}: 271 (1974). Stems 50-80 cm, with short or long hairs at base, slender; internodes long. Leaves 15-30 × 2-4 mm, lanceolate, relatively thin, with short, hyaline apiculum; midrib slender, comprising less than half the width of the leaf; margin slightly revolute and somewhat scabrid. Inflorescence broadly ovoid, lax, with long, patent to ascending branches; pedicels slender. Corolla 2-4 mm in diameter, usually yellowish. 2n = 44. •{\i  Mountains of S. Greece} ({\i Peloponnisos}). Gr.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28   Variable in habit and leaf-shape. A closely related plant with purplish flowers and longer, narrower, revolute leaves occurs in S.W. Peloponnisos; it appears to be diploid, and may merit specific rank.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 54. G. asparagifolium} Boiss. & Heldr. in Boiss., {\i Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov. }{\b 3}({\b 6}): 91 (1859). Stems slender, ascending, with short hairs; internodes not more than 3 cm. Leaves 10 × 0·5-0·8 mm, filiform, with a short, hyaline apiculum; midrib slender; margin slightly scabrid. Inflorescence narrow, with patent to erect, relatively long branches; pedicels 2-3 mm. Corolla 2-3 mm in diameter.{\i  Mountain rocks. S.C. & N. Greece.} Gr.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 55. G. melanantherum} Boiss., {\i Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov.}{\b  1}({\b 6}): 68 (1846-1847). Stems up to 50 cm, rigid, with prominent angles, nearly always with short hairs at base; internodes short below middle of stem, the upper longer. Leaves 10-15(-20) × 1(-2) mm, narrowly linear, coriaceous, shining; midrib prominent; margin strongly revolute, slightly scabrid. Inflorescence very lax, oblong, with short, erect branches; pedicels 5(-8) mm, slender. Corolla 5(-7) mm in diameter, greenish-purple. 2n = 22. {\i Dry, rocky places. • S.E. Greece.} Gr.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 56. G. rhodopeum} Velen., {\i Sitz.-Ber. Böhm. Ges. Wiss.} ({\i Math.Nat. Kl.}) {\b 1893} ({\b 37}): 32 (1893). Laxly caespitose, with densely leafy non-flowering shoots. Flowering stems 10-35 cm, mostly with short hairs, rigid and erect, with prominent, white ridges; internodes (7-)10-30(-40) mm. Leaves (5-)7-12(-15) × 0·5-1 mm, about as long as or longer than internodes, linear, acicular, gradually narrowed into a long hyaline apiculum. Inflorescence few-flowered, lax, long and narrow, with short, rigid, erect branches; pedicels (2-)2·5-5(-6) mm, slender. Corolla 3·5-4·5 (-5) mm in diameter, pale yellowish or white; lobes shortly apiculate. 2n = 22, 44. {\i Calcareous mountain cliffs. • C. part of E. Balkan peninsula.} Bu Gr Ju.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 57. G. incurvum} Sibth. & Sm.,{\i  Fl. Graec. Prodr.}{\b  1}: 92 (1806). Green or glaucous and pruinose. Stems 20-35(-40) cm, glabrous, ascending or erect; middle internodes usually shorter than leaves. Leaves 10-20(-30) × 2(-3) mm, linear-lanceolate, coriaceous or succulent, with short, hyaline apiculum; midrib prominent; margin revolute, slightly scabrid. Inflorescence often dense, with rigid, erect branches 3(-7) cm; pedicels 2-3 mm. Corolla up to 5 mm in diameter, yellowish or reddish; lobes shortly apiculate. 2n = 44.{\i  Rocky places. • S. Aegean region.} Cr Gr.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    It may be possible to separate the typical species from the higher mountains of Kriti, with slender habit, and incurved, linear, non-succulent green leaves, from {\b G. amorginum} Halácsy, {\i Consp. Fl. Graec. }{\b 1}: 712 (1901), comprising coastal populations of the S. Aegean with more robust growth, and linear-lanceolate, succulent, and often glaucous-pruinose leaves.
\par 

