\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 58. G. flavescens} Borbás,{\i  Akad. Közl.}{\b  11}({\b 7}): 266 (1874). Stems up to 80(-100) cm, robust, strongly branched from the base, glabrous or with short (very rarely long) hairs. Leaves 25-40 × 1 mm, narrowly linear; midrib prominent; margin strongly revolute, sharply scabrid. Inflorescence broadly ovoid, with numerous erect branches; pedicels up to 7 mm. Corolla up to 5 mm in diameter; lobes strongly apiculate. 2n = 44. {\i Dry places. From C. Romania to N. Macedonia.} Bu Ju Rm ?Tu.
