\pard\f0\fs28  Ser.{\i  Octonaria }(Klokov) Pobed. Plants glaucous-pruinose. Stems terete to 4-angled. Leaves linear to filiform, more rarely elliptical or oblanceolate, not more than 45 mm and often less than 25 mm, uniformly glaucous on upper and lower surfaces. Inflorescences broadly ovoid to pyramidal, with long lower branches; partial inflorescences usually corymbiform; pedicels rather stout, not divaricate after anthesis. Corolla white, infundibuliform to cup-shaped, with tube somewhat longer to much shorter than lobes; lobes acute, rarely shortly apiculate.
