\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 59. G. pruinosum} Boiss.,{\i  Elenchus} 57 (1838). Stolons absent. Stems 20-100 cm, more or less rounded, with 4 ridges, glabrous. Leaves 10-20 × 2-6 mm, in whorls of 5-7, elliptical to broadly lanceolate, somewhat coriaceous; margin with 1-2 rows of papillose teeth, revolute but not to the midrib. Inflorescence ovoid; partial inflorescences corymbiform, lax, few-flowered; pedicels shorter than diameter of corolla. Corolla 3-4 mm in diameter, infundibuliform; tube much shorter than lobes.{\i  Crevices of limestone cliffs. • Mountains of S. Spain.} Hs.
